text: Champaign County is a county in the U.S. state of Illinois. As of the 2020 census, the population was 205,865, making it the 10th-most populous county in Illinois. The county seat is Urbana. Champaign County was founded in 1833. == References == Category:1830s establishments in Illinois Category:1833 establishments in the United States Category:Illinois counties
